ğŸ”„ Fixing Stale/Corrupted Builds on Cloudflare Pages

Because Cloudflare may serve cached or stale JS bundles, you can fix JS initialization or hydration errors by doing any of the following:

Option A â€” Re-deploy latest build

Cloudflare Dashboard â†’ Pages â†’ justice-bot

Deployments â†’ Retry deployment

Option B â€” Force a new deploy

Make any small commit to GitHub (e.g. update this README).
Cloudflare will deploy a fresh build.

Option C â€” Purge cache

Cloudflare Dashboard â†’ Caching

Purge Everything

This clears stale JS/CSS bundles from Edge.

Option D â€” Full reset (rarely needed)

Delete the project on Cloudflare Pages â†’ re-create it pointing to the repo.

